<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-02-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-02-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="137" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d137">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 811.0151/42</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-02-12">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 12, 1915</hi>.</date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 10.25 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1631. Your telegram 1106 [1105], February 10, taken up with <persName corresp="#p_GSE1">Sir Edward Grey</persName> and a memorandum
                                embodying its request left with <pb facs="0360" n="102" xml:id="pg_102"/> him. He said that the Admiralty had already
                                received instructions which he thought practically complied with our
                                request but that he would answer more specifically as soon as he
                                could confer with the Cabinet and the Admiralty.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Ambassador</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>